&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse, Band 5 – Child Assessment Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, enthusiastic Paediatric nurse to complement our team of Band 5 staff within the Children’s Assessment Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit welcomes a wide variety of acutely sick children who require rapid assessment, treatment and follow up as day patients. The Unit covers a variety of specialities including general medicine, surgery, orthopaedics, oncology and neonates, and we perform and assist in various tests and investigations. Working across the unit, you will have the opportunity to develop your acute clinical and managerial skills in a supportive environment that values the contribution of individuals. If you have a high level of motivation and the forward-thinking approach needed to influence quality of care, in a fast moving unit, we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our current shift patterns are 07.30 until 20.00 and 12.00 until 24.00 (mon-fri) and 07.30 until 20.00 (weekends).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For enquiries, or to arrange an informal visit, contact Unit Manager Sharon Chambers on 01737 768511 ext 2813 or 2878/9&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 11/11/2020 (midnight)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 26/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
